[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'A repo called Open Code Sign hit 2,334 GitHub stars in 7 days. It is an Electron desktop app that turns prompts into shippable HTML pages, PDFs, and PowerPoint decks. Multi-model, bring your own key, fully local.'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The whole thing is positioned as an open-source alternative to Claude design. And importantly, it is not affiliated with Anthropic. Different team, different org, MIT licensed. Let\'s break down what it does, why it is'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'trending, and what to know before you install a 1-week-old desktop app. Open Code Sign is a desktop app. Electron-based, ships .dmg for macOS, .exe for Windows, app image and deb and'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'rpm for Linux. You install it, you bring an API key for whichever model you want to use, Anthropic, OpenAI, Gemini, DeepSeek, Kimiko, GLM, Ollama, Open Router, or any OpenAI-compatible'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'endpoint. The headline feature is a one-click import that reads your existing Claude code or Codex config, and pulls in providers, models, and keys automatically. 12 built-in design skill modules,'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dashboards, landing pages, slide decks, SVG charts, glassmorphism, editorial typography, heroes, pricing pages, footers, chat UIs, data tables, calendars.'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You type a prompt, the agent panel streams tool calls live, and you get an exportable artifact in under a minute. Installation has three platform-native paths, macOS, brew install dash dash cask open-cowork-ai/tap/open-code-sign.'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Windows, winget install open-cowork-ai.open-code-design. Linux, you get the app image from the v0.1.4 GitHub release, chmod +x, run it. After install, launch the app, click'

[01:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'import from Claude code, and the app auto-detects your tilde/.claude/settings.json file and pulls in your providers and keys automatically. No retyping API keys. No reconfiguring models. The'

[01:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'first-run experience is genuinely friction-free if you have already configured Claude code on the machine. If you have a Codex config instead, the same import flow detects that, too. Both paths land you in the same place. Here\'s'

[02:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the feature that maps perfectly to a mobile view. Open Code Sign ships built-in preview frames, desktop, tablet, and phone, side-by-side with the full canvas. When the agent generates a landing page or a dashboard, you do not'

[02:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have to imagine what it looks like at 430 pixels wide. The phone frame renders the actual artifact at iPhone proportions in real-time. Same for tablet. That responsive preview is what the team highlights on the'

[02:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'marketing site. And it is what differentiates Open Code Sign from a generic prompt to HTML pipeline. You see the responsive story before you export. Designers who have to ship for mobile-first audiences get a real'

[02:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'workflow win out of the box. The product site at open-cowork-ai.github.io/open-code-sign is itself responsive. And it is a clean live demo of the responsive design philosophy the app is built on. Scroll'

[03:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'through it on mobile, and you see the same patterns the app generates. Hero with screenshot. Feature blocks with phone frame screenshots. Skill module gallery. Provider list. Install commands per platform. The whole site is a meta'

[03:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'demonstration of what you can build with the tool. Worth scrolling through on a real phone before you install. If the site itself feels like the kind of artifact you want to ship, that is your strongest signal that the tool fits your'

[03:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'workflow. Conversely, if you scroll through and think the design language is not yours, save yourself the install. GitHub repo at github.com/open-cowork-ai/open-code-sign. TypeScript at 90.5%'

[03:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'MIT licensed. 530 commits across the past week. That is roughly 75 commits per day, which is wild velocity for a brand new project. v0.1.4 and added three things worth calling'

[03:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out. GPT image-to-image generation, ChatGPT plus OAuth login, so you do not need to manage an API key separately if you have a plus subscription. And Claude proxy API auto-detection.'

[04:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '47 open issues already, proportional to age, but real. The release notes for v0.1.4 mention a big reliability wave, which tells you the earlier 0.1.x versions had genuine rough edges.'

